  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Kamla Nehru Memorial Trust & Anr. versus U.P. State Industrial Development Corporation Limited & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_5_673_695','2025INSC791'); ><font size='4'> <strong>KAMLA NEHRU MEMORIAL TRUST & ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>U.P. STATE INDUSTRIAL DEVELOPMENT CORPORATION LIMITED & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 673</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 791</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010004212025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SURYA KANT<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, N KOTISWAR SINGH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The central issue concerns the legality of the cancellation of allotment by Uttar Pradesh State Industrial Development Corporation (UPSIDC). Whether UPSIDC is responsible for frustrating the performance of the the cancellation of allotment of the subject land was procedurally defective and legally untenable. Headnotes&dagger; Allotment of Land &ndash; Cancellation of allotment &ndash; Legality of &ndash; Appellant-KNMT was allotted subject land by UPSIDC &ndash; The allotment letter required KNMT to<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 30-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 7273/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_5_673_695','2025INSC791','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split vi